sentences: Indu Mitha (née Chatterjee) (born 1929) is a Pakistani exponent of Bharatnatyam and one of only two in the nation (the other being Sheema Kirmani).
Indu Mitha was born Indu Chatterjee in a Bengali Christian family in 1929.
She studied MA philosophy from Delhi University in 1951.
In 1951, she married Captain Aboobaker Osman Mitha, a Mumbai Memon against the wishes of her family, and moved back to Pakistan with him.
Mitha received President’s Award for Pride of Performance Awards (2020–2029) in August, 2020.
Mitha received President’s Award for Pride of Performance Awards (2020–2029) in August, 2020.
In the years following her husband's retirement, Mitha began teaching Bharatnatyam in Lahore.
She now does one show a year for private audiences, mostly all-women groups, due to the heightened atmosphere linked to the rise of the Taliban.
